HOOSIER MANUFACTURING COMPANY v. NATIONAL LABOR RELATIONS BOARD, United Brotherhood of Carpenters, and Joiners of America, Local No. 1761, Hoosier Employees Association. No. 5513. Circuit Court of Appeals, Seventh Circuit. June 13, 1935. Albert Stump, of Indianapolis, Ind., for petitioner. Harold M. Stephens, of Washington, D. C., for respondent.

Before SPARKS and ALSCHULER, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon the motion of the petitioner, made pursuant to stipulation on file in the above cause, it is ordered by the court that the above cause and the petition therein be, and the same are hereby, dismissed, without prejudice.. . •
